page.title: 04HOUSING, CANAL HEAD
page.content: HOUSING. Canal head. pop. included in Pocklington figures. This is a Hamlet of 14 dwellings and one pub.There is also an old corn mill,although not now in use for milling it is very well preserved, and was still operating until approx.,1945 (Devonshire Mill). Bar snacks, Diners, Luncheons are served at the Wellington Oak, this is an early 19th century pub with a fine collection of Brass Kitchen Utensils,(the owners being collectors).At Canel Head there is an Agricultural Engineer and Scrap Dealer who's hobby is repairing and restoring horse drawn caravans.This is the head of the Canal, it has a picnic area with tables & chairs, the houses have window boxes, colourful gardens & flower filled tubs. As in the rest of this area the surrounding land is farmed.
